</taxonomicName>
species from 
<collectingCountry box="[800,867,1507,1532]" name="China" pageId="2" pageNumber="237">China</collectingCountry>
and adjacent regions. Three of these species have hairs on the dorsal surface of the scutellum, in common with 
<taxonomicName box="[842,984,1543,1567]" class="Insecta" family="Conopidae" genus="Zodion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="237" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="andersoni">
<emphasis box="[842,984,1543,1567]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="237">Z. andersoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: 
<taxonomicName authority="Chen, 1939" authorityName="Chen" authorityYear="1939" box="[1000,1345,1542,1567]" class="Insecta" family="Conopidae" genus="Zodion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="237" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigricorne">
<emphasis box="[1000,1205,1543,1567]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="237">Zodion nigricorne</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Chen" box="[1212,1345,1542,1567]" pageId="2" pageNumber="237" refString="Chen, S. H. (1939) Etude sur les Dipteres Conopides de la Chine. Notes d' Entomologie Chinoise, 6, 161 - 231." type="journal article" year="1939">
Chen, 
<number box="[1286,1345,1543,1567]" pageId="2" pageNumber="237" value="1939.0">1939</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Chen, 1939" authorityName="Chen" authorityYear="1939" class="Insecta" family="Conopidae" genus="Zodion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="237" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rufipes">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="237">Zodion rufipes</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Chen" box="[236,368,1579,1604]" pageId="2" pageNumber="237" refString="Chen, S. H. (1939) Etude sur les Dipteres Conopides de la Chine. Notes d' Entomologie Chinoise, 6, 161 - 231." type="journal article" year="1939">
Chen, 
<number box="[309,368,1579,1603]" pageId="2" pageNumber="237" value="1939.0">1939</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName authority="Chen, 1939" authorityName="Chen" authorityYear="1939" box="[427,742,1579,1604]" class="Insecta" family="Conopidae" genus="Zodion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="237" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pilosum">
<emphasis box="[427,602,1579,1603]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="237">Zodion pilosum</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Chen" box="[610,742,1579,1604]" pageId="2" pageNumber="237" refString="Chen, S. H. (1939) Etude sur les Dipteres Conopides de la Chine. Notes d' Entomologie Chinoise, 6, 161 - 231." type="journal article" year="1939">
Chen, 
<number box="[683,742,1579,1603]" pageId="2" pageNumber="237" value="1939.0">1939</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. To distinguish between these three species 
<bibRefCitation author="Chen" box="[1237,1377,1579,1604]" pageId="2" pageNumber="237" refString="Chen, S. H. (1939) Etude sur les Dipteres Conopides de la Chine. Notes d' Entomologie Chinoise, 6, 161 - 231." type="journal article" year="1939">
Chen (
<number box="[1311,1369,1579,1603]" pageId="2" pageNumber="237" value="1939.0">1939</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
used the colouration of the tarsi and the tip of the abdomen. 
<taxonomicName box="[784,984,1615,1639]" class="Insecta" family="Conopidae" genus="Zodion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="237" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="andersoni">
<emphasis box="[784,984,1615,1639]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="237">Zodion andersoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
—the original description of which was cited by 
<bibRefCitation author="Chen" box="[254,400,1651,1676]" pageId="2" pageNumber="237" refString="Chen, S. H. (1939) Etude sur les Dipteres Conopides de la Chine. Notes d' Entomologie Chinoise, 6, 161 - 231." type="journal article" year="1939">
Chen (
<number box="[332,392,1651,1675]" pageId="2" pageNumber="237" value="1939.0">1939</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, but which was not included in his key—accords with his 
<taxonomicName box="[1091,1213,1651,1675]" class="Insecta" family="Conopidae" genus="Zodion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="237" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pilosum">
<emphasis box="[1091,1213,1651,1675]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="237">Z. pilosum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. However the 
<typeStatus box="[1388,1436,1652,1676]" pageId="2" pageNumber="237">type</typeStatus>
material of 
<taxonomicName box="[279,397,1687,1711]" class="Insecta" family="Conopidae" genus="Zodion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="237" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pilosum">
<emphasis box="[279,397,1687,1711]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="237">Z. pilosum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was not available to me for this study and should be checked before any formal synonymy is introduced.
